snippet.textDisplay: To say Manchester City were robbed is completely wrong, that’s what happens when you don’t take your chances. There’s no excuse for having 10+ shots and  a couple open nets but missing all of them. At the end of the day, it’s not about who controls the ball or who has more possession or whoever spent the most time in the opposition’s half, it’s about who can take their chances and score. After all, you don’t get points for playing better football, it’s about who can actually take and convert their chances.
